D.q[2950] = "What? How is this possible? Why would you want to break the eternal, sacred bond of marriage? I hope you have a good reason.";
D.q[675] = "So you know the summoning of the cross-stitc... I mean the summoning of the Chaferfu... Chaferfu said... say Hello!";
D.q[3848] = "Adventurers often stop by taverns and Inns to recover some energy and knock back a nice, refreshing Incarnam Lemonade.";
D.q[422] = "Swords are the favourite weapons of Ecaflips and Iops. To handle such swords you must be very strong, but they often cause great damage.\nSword Smiths use the Sword Smith Hammer.";
D.q[6363] = "The what? I don\'t go out very often, you know. I prefer this dark, quiet place to the annoying bustle of the sea port.";
D.q[3106] = "Thanks for all these services. You might think I\'m a bit moody, but If I said yes to everyone, I\'d be running around just like you are! My metabolism would never stand it, either.";
D.q[4156] = "Thanks to you, I know why my son tried to get away from me. I\'ve learnt my lesson well and will never ever call him my sweet wabbit again. From now one I\'ll call him my little Gobbly... I\'m sure he\'ll love it!";
D.q[1835] = "Thank you! I made a nice raft with the items you brought me. I\'ll be able to leave the island very soon!";
D.q[2941] = "Adventurer, beware! Terrible creatures live inside this dungeon. Unless you\'re a group of at least three adventurers, you won\'t survive! Are you sure you want to enter?";
D.q[3905] = "Everything\'s going as planned.";
D.q[658] = "You\'re wrong! Death, when provoked or simulated, CANNOT break off the indestructible bounds of marriage! Oh... You weren\'t talking about that?...\nRegarding the funerals, the management doesn\'t take care of anything. In fact, once dead you\'ll have to go to the cemetery and find a grave for yourself. God buries those who bury themselves...";
D.q[1374] = "Thanks, let\'s begin...... But... Djaul\'s Blood! The lava is not displaying the properties it should! The evidence suggests that the magma current is shifting! We must find out what\'s really happening. There\'s a cave to the south-east of here. A river of lava flows deep inside it. I think it will be the best place to examine this phenomenon. Unfortunately, the cave is infested with monsters, so you\'ll take me there and act as my guardian.";
D.q[5465] = "Bear enter tavern. Bear say Me want Astrub Beer...";
D.q[5193] = "Me freee! You want me follow you?";
D.q[7296] = "";
D.q[1246] = "Well, I\'m warning you... This is the last time I turn a blind eye to the origin of this recipe, but you shouldn\'t take advantage of my kindness...";
D.q[1764] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Enutrofs. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is. ";
D.q[6976] = "Hello, have you got hold of what I asked you for?";
D.q[4303] = "Are you sure you want to go back where I took you? Do you remember how dangerous that place is? \nI\'ll take you back there if you bring me a Barkritter Calyx.";
D.q[1435] = "While I was feeding the Snappers this morning, my ring fell in the water. It happens to me all the time.";
D.q[741] = "I\'m down in the dumps right now.\nAsk Captain Essacarf if he needs help...";
D.q[3171] = "Diamondine? Is it you? I can\'t see you! Please come closer!";
D.q[4017] = "Good, here\'s your outfit.";
D.q[6786] = "If that tickles your fancy...";
D.q[7851] = "The fishermen claim that the Pingwins, appalled by their extermination since the arrival of people from the continent, and the insult to their king, have mounted a punitive expedition.\nOf course at first I didn\'t believe them, until I saw the expedition in question with my own eyes.\nPrepare for battle and then come and help me repel them.";
D.q[7024] = "Damn, I\'ll have to wait a bit longer, then.\nI\'ll watch over the paddock and I have to make sure that no one takes the path behind me without being properly equipped.";
D.q[451] = "So he called on the Order of the Kicked Ass to exchange, without the consent of his customers, these famously over-powerful boots for the Ultrapowerful Boots of Klime... which are just as powerful but more difficult to wear.\n\nThe Order of the Kicked Ass had to carry out a large scale operation which was not easy. Many clients noticed the difference in the boots and started to hunt down and to threaten the poor shoemaker. Since then he\'s left Amakna for good...\nNowadays, it\'s the Order of the Kicked Ass that operates customer services and helps people who have difficulties wearing their Ultrapowerful Boots of Klime by exchanging them for some Powerful Boots of Klime - a new model which is very fashionable at the moment. If you wish to exchange yours, don\'t hesitate, come see me.";
D.q[845] = "Apparently, there have been many crumblings in the sewers. Though the ground is quite unstable around here, it\'s rumoured that these crumblings aren\'t natural. Check it.";
D.q[7380] = "I\'m starting to get fed up with incompetent idiots. I\'ll get rid of this annoyance for you, although I don\'t think the lesson will bear fruit.";
D.q[1834] = "All my Dopples are tired at the moment, come back tomorrow if you want to practice some more...";
D.q[6977] = "Excellent, this is a very good start. It looks promising for the rest.\nI think you deserve this small advance. It\'s not much, but you\'ll get more when the Dawn Shard has been forged.\nCome see me when you have regained your strength.";
D.q[6978] = "I hope everything goes well with Danathor. If he asks you to do too much or if you have a problem, please let me know. Even though I am your leader, I am also a friend and you can count on my support.";
D.q[1795] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[7297] = "";
D.q[7852] = "I haven\'t got time to talk, a new wave of Pingwins is coming. Heal yourself and get ready to fight.";
D.q[6979] = "What are you doing here? Danathor\'s been waiting for you for a while now.\nWell, if he asks me why you\'re late, I\'ll tell him that I asked you to run an urgent errand for me. Now bugger off, there\'s no point hanging around here.";
D.q[5179] = "";
D.q[7853] = "We\'ve repelled the Pingwins and suffered minimal damage in the process. Some fisherman fell off the cliffs during the fight but the human casualties were less than 7%, which is acceptable.\nThe Pingwins should leave us alone for a while. I think Damar should take the opportunity to reopen the supply lines to Frigost. Why don\'t you go and see him?";
D.q[394] = "Hi, I\'m Ali Akelle, a painter and illustrator. My illustrations are in black and white, and I use powdered Arachnee Legs to make my paints. By the way, I really need some powder right now... I\'ve put in an order, but...";
D.q[3469] = "Bworks want to feed Trool with Raxitik. Me don\'t want *sniff sniff*, me have 19 minigobs to feed *sniff*...";
D.q[5205] = "";
D.q[7026] = "I remember that someone knew how to make them but I can\'t remember who exactly. I\'ve thought it about it lots, but I can\'t remember his name. It must be because I\'m tired. I hope the new shift arrives soon so I can get some rest.";
D.q[249] = "That\'s not my priority for the moment, but you can pass the time with our Dopples in the meanwhile. Go see Brigitebardo Pull, she\'s the one who raises them.";
D.q[7298] = "";
D.q[3154] = "Hello #1. I\'m Fidji Merline, Liroye Merline\'s sister and one of the most famous handywomen on the continent. My family has been doing things for itself for generations now, \'handying\' as we call it. Recently my sister and I decided to set up a business. Since we want to share what handiness we know with everyone, we\'ve decided to only open shops in enemy cities. Well, what handy hints do you want to know?";
D.q[7027] = "Wait, let me think...\nThere! Sag Dratsum the Enutrof knows how to make them. I think he went to work in Terrdala village, you should go there.\nI can\'t wait for the next shift to take over, I\'m knackered.";
D.q[1281] = "What a waste! Heavens, did you peel them with a sabre or what?!";
D.q[1518] = "So be it.\nBring this letter to Oto Mustam.";
D.q[4912] = "Nosilla Budois is the only medium I know, I guess it\'s her you\'re talking about.\nShe was a good friend, but I found her little soft, for a Sacrier.";
D.q[6980] = "You\'ve arrived just in time to set off on a search for a Dragon\'s Remembrance Fragments. Yes, I did just say \"a Dragon\'s Remembrance Fragments\", and I don\'t care how you go about it.\nIt appears that you have rescued a Sacrier with a divinatory talent that would make a Xelor blush, why don\'t you ask her? She probably knows a way to capture Remembrance Fragments, after all, it is her domain.";
D.q[7299] = "";
D.q[5996] = "For your sake, I hope you have some good news.";
D.q[1462] = "Good work #1! I knew I could rely on you, but as soon as you accept your mission, you won\'t be able to change your mind...";
D.q[1766] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Osamodas. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[241] = "I told you that I wouldn\'t say a word! I\'ll never tell you... believe me, it\'s well hidden... oh yeesss, in a cave, the entrance of which is in the shadow of a glowing bush. Aargh. Damn... well, the entry is sealed anyway. Good thing I can\'t remember where that bush is...";
D.q[7300] = "";
D.q[1522] = "So be it.\nBring this letter to Oto, and carry on your way.";
D.q[7301] = "";
D.q[7028] = "It was a good job you showed me your Sag Mask. Look here, it\'s split. A little bit more and you\'d be heading for certain death.\nGo and see Sag Dratsum in Terrdala Village, he should be able to repair it for you. As for me, I\'ll try not to fall asleep waiting for the next shift.";
D.q[3772] = "Just try! Don\'t worry, it\'s just practice!";
D.q[2173] = "Thank you very much! This meeting was of the highest importance. Take these Kamas as a reward. Come back whenever you want. I\'ll give you some of my precious time.";
D.q[4433] = "Hi!";
D.q[6464] = "You want a few copies of the key? I can help you, but you\'ll have to bring me 5 Planks of Cherry Wood so I can repair the machines in the public paddocks. There aren\'t enough private paddocks and many breeders are forced to use the public facilities. So many people on so few machines means trouble, and I\'m responsible for repairing them when they break down - which is very often. I can\'t let people use faulty machinery. Imagine all the leather on a Dragobutt is worn and a Iop tries to use it... can you imagine the damage that would cause?";
D.q[691] = "And the final question,\nbefore assessing the situation.\nOf cuddles we are talking.\nMorning, midday or evening ?";
D.q[7302] = "";
D.q[5208] = "";
D.q[408] = "A shoemaker essentially works leather to make belts but also boots. \nSometimes shoemakers use wood and rare metals to either decorate or reinforce their creations.\nShoemakers use a dagger called Leather Cutter to work leather.\nIf you\'re looking for a tool like that, I can give you one for a little help.";
D.q[5104] = "";
D.q[7478] = "";
D.q[1120] = "Thanks, the goddess Jiva thanks you.";
D.q[4904] = "Pnj(679) et Message(4903)";
D.q[4153] = "Thanks to your genius idea, I managed to save a lot of time and quality flour. I hope that you now understand why I\'m one of the best bakers of the World of Twelve.";
D.q[7025] = "The air in and around Brakmar is not known to be particularly good for your lungs, but is nothing compared to this region. The air is saturated with sulphur and toxic fumes escaping from the bowels of the earth, and that\'s without mentioning the few creatures that live there and who, maddened by the air they breathe continuously, attack anything they see as food on first sight.\nIf you\'re not experienced enough and you do not have a Sag Mask, you will not survive a second, and going alone would be suicide.";
D.q[7303] = "";
D.q[5180] = "";
D.q[7479] = "";
D.q[7367] = "";
D.q[721] = "Thanks to your last observations, I think I\'ve found a way of breaching Brakmar\'s door. I\'ll present my report to my superiors. Thank you.";
D.q[3496] = "Bworkid be paxifik.";
D.q[7309] = "";
D.q[7368] = "";
D.q[2353] = "Well, all \'know is that the council asked us to patrol in those damn underpasses... \'Must know more about this stuff than me, that\'s for sure! And the old legends are not going to calm things down, betcha!";
D.q[3691] = "All clear. I haven\'t seen a thing.";
D.q[7480] = "";
D.q[7304] = "";
D.q[7481] = "";
D.q[1576] = "Have mercy! I want out of this squalid prison!";
D.q[5610] = "I\'s startin\' to hallucinate. That\'s it, old Terra Cogita\'s losin\' it.";
D.q[4910] = "Good day to you, to what do I owe this visit?";
D.q[6983] = "Hello, I am Farmhand Ruprecht, an expert on dragons and strong drinks.\nI am currently working on a thesis on how the pigmentation of Dreggons changes according to their diet. It is a truly fascinating subject.\nUnfortunately I do not much time to spend with you, but if we meet each other at the Captain Chafer Panty Party, I will certainly buy you a drink.";
D.q[4311] = "";
D.q[4349] = "";
D.q[7305] = "";
D.q[4824] = "With all that you found during your investigation, there\'s no doubt that Kit Dingaround will be acquitted.";
D.q[7854] = "Fortunately, we can count on Mel for the site\'s safety. When she was still a little girl, she amused herself clearing scree with a spade.\nSince the Pingwin threat has been eliminated for the moment, we are able to supply our citizens safely.\nGo see Al Fabeticorder and tell him that the distribution of Icefish can resume.";
D.q[5223] = "";
D.q[2008] = "Ow! Stop that...You don\'t have a clue how to do it. We\'re going to get in trouble if it belongs to someone. Poor Gobball, it died on the spot. I don\'t think anyone\'s seen you. Go and give the bow to Dragonsly, the alchemist, he\'ll improve the string. I mean... If it really comes from the bow...";
D.q[6984] = "Hey, you! Get me out of here!\nThere is a lever on the floor. Activate it so that I can escape.\nIf you do that for me, you can come over to my house and have a drink as often as you like. My house is located in Breeder Village in the Koalak region.";
D.q[6811] = "You mean that stinking Sram and his indecent proposals? I don\'t know anything about him, it was the first, and hopefully the last time I saw him.";
D.q[6482] = "That\'s very nice of you, but orders are orders. I can\'t show you the report. I can tell you that the original report is in the Tower of Bonta. I\'m not allowed go and have a look at it to make sure it\'s the real thing which is unusual since I\'m the expert on that kind of thing. If someone went and stole it I could see whether it was authentic or not if someone went and stole them for me though... There are plenty of guards though, that\'s the problem. Someone as tricky as yourself could steal them I\'m sure, even if there were guards about, am I wrong? Well, I probably at least.";
D.q[6217] = "I don\'t know what you\'re talking about. I never go into the tower of Bonta. Was it Bagrutte who told you about me. I\'ll teach him to get mixed up in my business.";
D.q[3581] = "Me no sick.";
D.q[7306] = "";
D.q[4920] = "It depends on who\'s going to be the doll, hehe.";
D.q[5689] = "The Brakmarians know where the statues are. Please reassure me and tell me you\'ve managed to find one?";
D.q[477] = "Wobot, wegimental numbew 53, pwivate fwom the eleventh wobot wegiment of the Wa Guawd.\nHalt! Who goes thewe?\n";
D.q[7828] = "Ensuring the safety of the fishermen was much easier in the past. After the crater was flooded with hot water, it filled up with fish. Fishing was thus a very important activity here. But since it froze over, it\'s become very difficult to make a living.\nIn the past, you only needed to worry about the forest creatures. Now you must resist the incessant onslaught of Pingwins that steal thawed out fish.";
D.q[6985] = "Hello... wait, I know you. Oh yes! It was you who helped me out of the Brakmar prison. How can I thank you?";
D.q[1857] = "The creation of new clothes is quite hard. Make clothes using a pattern is already easier, if that... A good tailor must have a good network of suppliers, otherwise he won\'t do much. Furthermore, skills and experience are required to make the best clothes for important people.";
D.q[5460] = "Me starving! Me want Apple!";
D.q[7830] = "Couldn\'t you find anything else?\nThat stupid Gerard, he died like he lived.\nHmmm, I don\'t know about you, but I\'m hungry now.";
D.q[7307] = "";
D.q[3434] = "The El children? No. I haven\'t seen them.";
D.q[953] = "The door of this tower is in the northwest of Bonta. It contains all the civil services of the city.\nIf you\'re looking for the treasurer or the mayor of Bonta, you\'ll certainly find them over there.";
D.q[7310] = "";
D.q[3912] = "A noble? There are a lot of nobles here, but none of them seems worthy of the princess.";
D.q[92] = "Hyooohooo, I need to make a pair of leather braces to stop my loincloth falling down. Bring me some Gobball leather and I\'ll give you my Staff Slasher in exchange. You\'ll be able to carve staffs with it, if you\'ve learnt the appropriate profession.";
D.q[1703] = "The Enutrof temple is located north of the village of Amakna. Talk to Elisa Granite to begin your training.";
D.q[7311] = "";
D.q[5790] = "";
D.q[1047] = "Heh, you seem to be keen on cannons ? I know everything there is to know about them.";
D.q[4117] = "Can you cross your arms?";
D.q[5793] = "Sorry, sorry, false alarm. Pfff!";
D.q[7678] = "Oh, what to do! My cellar is full of Faded Stunted Rats and in addition to making a terrible noise, they create a terrible smell that attracts all of the Bow Wows in the neighbourhood! It scares my Kiki, and when my Kiki is scared, I\'m not happy!";
D.q[1478] = "Heheh, well done. I\'ll give it to our recruitment team. They\'ll be pleased.";
D.q[6921] = "Nosilla claimed to be plagued by visions and always at the most inopportune moments, like in a battle against the Bworker and his Cybworks. Nevertheless, Nosilla\'s visions seemed very real and they got my group and I out of unfortunate situations on more than one occasion, not to mention the treasures they uncovered.";
D.q[4749] = "Here, take this, it\'s a note for your judge. Don\'t bother me with such trifling matters in future.";
D.q[7312] = "";
D.q[5791] = "";
D.q[7684] = "Another tourist ... You saw the light when you came in, right? I don\'t understand why Seth Leurse, my predecessor, didn\'t put any locks on the door.\nWell, since you\'re here, you can make yourself useful. Some creatures are disturbing the tranquillity of Frigost but I don\'t have the time to decimate all of them. Do you feel like giving me a hand?";
D.q[7313] = "";
D.q[5226] = "";
D.q[749] = "The inhabitants of the city are getting fed up of William Lenglad and his merry band. Give them a good hiding and you\'ll make me a happy man.\nYou\'ll find him west of Bonta.";
D.q[7685] = "Hello, you find yourself in front of the hottest spot on the island, apart from the volcano, of course. We use the greenhouses to cultivate new plants that would not survive the freezing temperatures of the island, and especially to be able to replant them when the ice age is over.\nUnfortunately, hungry Mastogobs have taken up residence in the greenhouses, in search of food, and they have become aggressive because of the heat. They began to attack staff and devour the plants, even to graze my wife\'s lawn, who was director of the greenhouse, you see?\nIn exchange for the key to the greenhouse, I can let you in to give the Royal Mastogob a good kicking, but beware! It\'s got quite used to its cosy life and seems to have disproportionate reactions when it is moved.";
D.q[7706] = "Hello, if you think I\'ll let you use my carrier, you\'ve got another thing coming. Prove to me that you\'re trustworthy and then maybe, I say maybe, I\'ll let you climb aboard.";
D.q[4016] = "A servant\'s outfit for a Wabbit prince? That\'s quite an unusual order. I don\'t have the materials. I need some crimson fabric, like the one we find on Bwork Magi. I\'ll assemble it all with ten silk strings. If you find that for me, I can make you an outfit worthy of a prince\'s servant.";
D.q[4913] = "Nosilla Budois? Although I am not proud of what happened to her, I stayed true to my principles. But you\'d probably prefer it if I started at the beginning, no?";
D.q[3199] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the eleventh room, or maybe in the twelfth one, or was it in the fifteenth? or the sixteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[7856] = "Did Al Fabeticorder send us that? I thought that oaf hated us. Perhaps he\'s not as narrow-minded as I thought.\nThank him for me.";
D.q[7857] = "Yuk, that\'s disgusting. These Icefish are already digested, we couldn\'t possibly eat them.";
D.q[5182] = "";
D.q[3987] = "Hell! A pwincess to mawwy! What intewesting news. I\'m youw pwince! Let\'s go now!";
D.q[2485] = "Thanks a lot! We can get back to work now... (he yawns).\n";
D.q[3198] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the eleventh room, or maybe in the twelfth one, or was it in the fifteenth? or the sixteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3195] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the eleventh room, or maybe in the twelfth one, or was it in the fifteenth? or the sixteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[5518] = "What can I do for you, Brakmarian?";
D.q[7314] = "";
D.q[1859] = "Thanks a lot... Here - that\'s the kind of cloak you can make with that. Try it on!!!\nOh. My. God... you look sooo cute! AAAARGH! But you need a lining for wintertime! I\'ll use some regular Gobball wool, less pretty but it\'ll keep your cheeks nice and toasty for the winter. Bring me your cloak and 5 balls of wool and I\'ll take care of it... Can I? Oh say yes! ";
D.q[4754] = "Your judge takes me for a crump...trump...frump...in short, tell him I\'m not for sale.";
D.q[7858] = "Remember that a Pingwobble\'s digestive process starts 30 minutes after it swallows something, so you need to finish delivering the Icefish before then.";
D.q[4375] = "";
D.q[3194] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the eleventh room, or maybe in the twelfth one, or was it in the fifteenth? or the sixteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[3865] = "Hello. I see you\'re a valiant warrior... Would you like to help us protect Amakna and Allister\'s throne?";
D.q[7315] = "";
D.q[3355] = "Hey, hey! You don\'t have a Key!";
D.q[4755] = "";
D.q[5237] = "Have you finished?";
D.q[5234] = "";
D.q[7859] = "Hello.";
D.q[5298] = "";
D.q[4411] = "Ah... ehhh, hello. What was that? What am I doing here? Well, I\'m having a look round the tower... I\'m allowed, no?";
D.q[7860] = "We haven\'t eaten Icefish for a long time, it\'ll make a nice change from Kanigloo croquettes.\nThanks be to you and the fishermen.";
D.q[1189] = "The Order of the Salvatory Spirit masters complex magic and healing.\nWe devote ourselves to others and to the protection of the city against evil attacks from Brakmarian Hecate followers.";
D.q[7861] = "Are you sure this is fresh Icefish? I get the impression it\'s been dipped in gastric juices...";
D.q[6449] = "The council won\'t give me permission to send troops to invade the bandits\' hideout. I\'m sure that there must be some information on the identity of their commander... I just can\'t send the troops without their damn permission... So I... the mission I\'m going to give you\'ll be dangerous, but I\'ve no choice.";
D.q[5191] = "";
D.q[7862] = "Fresh, juicy Icefish, the customers will love it.\nThat\'ll cheer Truffo\'s wife up no end.\nCan you imagine it - she kept a little secret grassy garden in one of the greenhouses, but the Royal Mastogob destroyed it all. She\'s been depressed ever since that day, and Truffo wants that beast\'s hide.";
D.q[868] = "58";
D.q[6365] = "The Panta Maria has been at sea for a long time and as far as I know the ship isn\'t scheduled to dock on Otomai Island for at least two weeks. It wasn\'t supposed to visit the Port of Madrestam at all. \nAs for Bonta, an important cargo of equipment left our workshops a week ago and should just about be arriving in the city about now. The militiamen are surely testing their new equipment.";
D.q[7863] = "Er, it\'s that really Icefish? It looks like the slop served up by Walter Aygo. I think you\'ve got the delivery wrong.";
D.q[5265] = "";
D.q[4757] = "I am beautiful and I have no desire to be made the doll of an old pervert. Here, take your letter.";
D.q[7864] = "You\'ve done a great job, I\'ll bear you in mind for the next lot of deliveries.\nThanks to you, and if the god Enutrof is with us, we\'ll be able to catch as many fish as we need.";
D.q[1731] = "Sacriers can use any weapon, but will never be as skilful as a specialist. They\'re most comfortable with spells.";
D.q[781] = "71";
D.q[782] = "72";
D.q[882] = "72";
D.q[5114] = "";
D.q[428] = "Staffs are not effective in close combat but they give great power to their holder. \nThe Sadida and Feca classes are pretty good with Staffs. In general, they require a little strength and much intelligence to be handled.\nStaff Carvers use a Staff Gasher.";
D.q[1681] = "THE FASTEST LARVAE IN ALL AMAKNA! COME AND BET ON YOUR FAVOURITE LARVA! IT\'S CHEAP AND EASY! ROLL UP ROLL UP, I\'LL MAKE YOU RICH! Hello, do you want to watch a larva race for 40 Kamas?";
D.q[7745] = "Because of this sinister Xelor a perpetual winter settled on our beautiful island. He is weakening day by day and is gradually sinking into madness, so now\'s the opportunity to punish him.";
D.q[4937] = "Go ask all the inhabitants of the Milicluster and the surrounding area and then report back to me.";
D.q[7782] = "A little under a decade ago, the ticks awoke from their slumber. They have made their home on my calves, sheltered from the cold, protected by the thick wool of their hosts. I suspect them to be carrying a pathogen that makes my calves demented and aggressive.";
D.q[2105] = "The Seer Blow, of course! I\'ll become rich and famous with this spell! If you want to learn more about it, have a seat, take a beer and listen to me, my friend. This is a fantastic story!";
D.q[7784] = "Pay a visit to Oshima and explain our problem. He\'s an animal specialist and will surely find a solution... What, why are you looking at me like that?";
D.q[4068] = "Hi!";
D.q[4140] = "So, did you manage to find a Bulbish Potion?";
D.q[6923] = "Let\'s go back to the time I spent wandering the World of Twelve.\nOne day a Xelor and an Enutrof came to see me because they wanted to meet Nosilla. I served as their intermediary, but I did not know the real intentions of these visitors. In fact, it so happened that they had every intention of locking Nosilla away, and I helped them achieve their goal after losing a bet.";
D.q[790] = "80";
D.q[791] = "81";
D.q[890] = "80";
D.q[7316] = "";
D.q[2650] = "The Pandasiman, or The dodging shield is one of the Pandawushus\' best schools. Unlike the Feca shield art, which is a technique of pure protection, this school will teach you how to use your shield as a means of staving off attacks too. What\'s special about this art is that the shield is used actively and not just as defence.";
D.q[794] = "84";
D.q[7369] = "";
D.q[7629] = "A book about Goultard, and, more specifically, about his childhood? Yes, I have a copy. Unfortunately, you\'ll need to speak to Lethaline Sigisbul if you want to read it.";
D.q[479] = "The access to this pawt of the island is wesewved to the Wa. Away with you, wascally wogue!";
D.q[893] = "83";
D.q[7061] = "The following stones...";
D.q[7317] = "";
D.q[3961] = "The Tofu attack failed... I think we will play the rogue way and just poison this Deaw pwince with a Rasputin Cake.";
D.q[7866] = "We are especially lacking wood. Aspen is well suited to the climate and its colour is appropriate. However, I\'ve heard of an exotic wood that diffuses a sweet and soothing scent, it\'s called Kaliptus. I think that by combining these two woods, we\'ll get something truly unique.\nCould you get some for me? I doubt that you can carry everything we need, so I\'ll just ask you for 5 Aspen Wood and 1 Kaliptus Wood Plank.";
D.q[5247] = "";
D.q[7462] = "";
D.q[7060] = "The following stones...";
D.q[7062] = "The following stones...";
D.q[695] = "All you need is ponder over.\nCome back at a secret hour.\nBy a kiss you\'ll be supplied\nWith patience you\'ll be armed .";
D.q[5751] = "I\'ll take all the seeds and never mind the side effects, I\'ll make these piwis real beasts of war. In a few generations, they\'ll be killing machines.\nYour help is invaluable to the Order, which is now why you rank as one of the Supreme Champions.\nMay the courage of Menalt inspire you in battle.";
D.q[2800] = "The thought of your blood being spilt in such a cursed place is making it boil... Are you trying to get into the maze?";
D.q[7318] = "";
D.q[805] = "95";
D.q[7370] = "";
D.q[905] = "95";
D.q[7812] = "How did they lose their way?\nI\'m counting on you to bring me back the others safely.";
D.q[7815] = "Don\'t even think about touching my sister, or there\'ll be trouble, I can assure you.";
D.q[7319] = "";
D.q[7808] = "Ah, someone has arrived at last, we\'re saved!\nYou\'ll never guess what happened to us. While we were preparing to return to the village with a good supply of wood, we became victims of fate.\nWe lost our way and have been going round in circles ever since, unable to find our way. Wherever we went we would always end up back here without meaning to. But since you\'re here, you will be able to accompany us back, one by one.\nDidn\'t I say? The curse is even more powerful when we are in a group. Since you seem unaffected by the spell, you can guide us.\nStart with Sioux Staurme Sioux, I\'d prefer it if I knew she was safe first.";
D.q[1043] = "Well, this necklace is in very poor condition, it will cost 1,000 Kamas to fix.";
D.q[5361] = "";
D.q[2155] = "Here you go, take everything";
D.q[4943] = "";
D.q[5825] = "";
D.q[5362] = "";
D.q[5259] = "";
D.q[3277] = "This magnificent key can take you directly where the Soft Oak hides, or almost... Let\'s say that you might need to kill some nasty creatures meanwhile. Do you really want to go?";
D.q[4417] = "Hurry up! You shouldn\'t miss the meeting.";
D.q[7308] = "";
D.q[5941] = "";
D.q[2158] = "Here, I\'ll take everything back.";
D.q[7631] = "A book about Goultard, and, more specifically, about his childhood? Yes, I have a copy. Unfortunately, you\'ll need to speak to Grace Malcean if you want to read it.";
D.q[7867] = "Oh, I didn\'t think you would do it, you are really very helpful, thank you. We need more people like you here. For your trouble, I\'ll give you a discount when you come on vacation in our future hotel.";
D.q[4626] = "Well what are you waiting for? Go to Moon Island and find some clues! Get out of here!";
D.q[7320] = "";
D.q[6930] = "You must have found us by chance, unless you\'re here because you\'re hunting Dragoturkeys. Tell me, you\'re not hunting Dragoturkeys, at least not near my house, are you?";
D.q[5602] = "This idiot Merlanmagus will find nothing there but fire. As for you, you\'re now officially a Dark Spy. \nSo? Happy?";
D.q[7819] = "You OK? It doesn\'t hurt too much?\nLet\'s head back to town!";
D.q[1574] = "But you\'ve already got one!";
D.q[3452] = "I\'ve finished the Filtounga. Eat it, and get out of my kitchen!";
D.q[6457] = "That troublemaker? I remember him like it was yesterday. He was causing trouble in an inn and we arrested him. Then we got an order to let him go in the morning, supposedly because he was covered in ticks and fleas. It\'s the first time a prisoner has been let out for poor hygiene, believe me! But orders are orders.\nI told my men to keep a close eye on him and they reported that he was hanging around the Tower of Orders, but since he\'s temporarily on the straight and narrow, we haven\'t been able to pick him up!";
D.q[5352] = "";
D.q[6988] = "Greetings. Are the Memory Fragments in your possession?";
D.q[7321] = "";
D.q[7824] = "Cold, me? Never!\nI am Damar, the chief fisherman, Pingwin blood flows in my veins... by dint of drinking too much of it.\nIf you want to make yourself useful, stop asking stupid questions.";
D.q[7825] = "Gerard? No, it\'s been a while since I saw him. He his drunken friends make such a racket that you must be able to hear it over at the Count\'s Castle, so if he was around, everyone would know about it.\nGo and annoy the know-it-alls next door with your questions, we\'ve got work to do here.";
D.q[7371] = "";
D.q[640] = "This is a Fountain of Youth! It will restore some of your health points.\n\nWhen you fight monsters, you\'ll surely lose health points.\nYou can restore yourself with this fountain so long as you haven\'t reached level 6.";
D.q[4788] = "I was just curious, there\'s no harm in that.";
D.q[7827] = "That drunkard hasn\'t been to insult us for a while, so I assume he didn\'t come here looking for a fight.\nInstead of wasting your time searching for him, I suggest you find something more meaningful to do. However, if you really want to find him, go ask Mel. She\'s responsible for the safety of fishermen on site and if anything unusual happened, she would be the first to know.";
D.q[5747] = "";
D.q[6989] = "Once again, your success is a credit to our city. Since this object is now in our possession, I will find out how to get Remembrance Fragments from it. As for you, I advise you to regain strength before your next mission.";
D.q[1358] = "*Waves his hand*";
D.q[1014] = "Thanks! I know a certain someone who\'ll be eating Gobball steak again thanks to you.\nGive Amayiro my regards!";
D.q[316] = "Thank you, I really appreciate it but I have to cope on my own. If you could just find me ten Moskito Wings... They help me think. \nOf course, I\'ll reward you.";
D.q[4791] = "Well... I... you know... I wanted to catch him red-handed... you know?";
D.q[4967] = "";
D.q[7831] = "Hello, don\'t start telling me about farming, I don\'t want to hear about it.\nI invested a good portion of my wealth to buy the greenhouse and have exclusive access to it.\nDon\'t misunderstand, I\'m not selfish. I use the greenhouse to develop all kinds of plants with diverse uses. I also try to create edible plants resistant to Frigost\'s climate to fight against hunger and replace agriculture. Only alchemists can grow them and what has happened because of agriculture and Count Harebourg will not happen again.";
D.q[7323] = "";
D.q[7373] = "";
D.q[3520] = "Me become goblinmagus, me so strong!";
D.q[1557] = "Thanks but only a miracle could cure my Tabi.\nI\'ve asked all the greatest specialists, doctors, druids, even magi, but they couldn\'t help me.\nA miracle...That\'s all I\'m asking for...";
D.q[5291] = "";
D.q[7324] = "";
D.q[3303] = "Ignoramus! Just go walk your ignorance out to the new library in Brakmar! You\'ll find everything you need to know about fighting, magic and breeding techniques. There are also numerous old books with all sorts of useful advice for surviving in the wild.";
D.q[7634] = "Get out of my sight, you pathetic cockroach, before I crush you like the repugnant insect you are.";
D.q[7868] = "It\'s exhausting spending your days in the cold digging ice or waiting for a fish to stick its nose out of the water. It\'s nothing like the good old days when the water was warm and teeming with fish.";
D.q[7374] = "";
D.q[3462] = "This recipe is too hard to use. I was hoping to get rich by brewing Bwork Beer but I think I\'ll have to settle for Bwork breeding instead.";
D.q[2519] = "This fake dragon egg has come at just the right moment! How about we create genuine copies... Made in Pandala? We just need to paint Dragoturkey eggs. Adventurers will never find out! They\'ll sell like hot Amakna cakes, believe me! Ahah, I\'m a genius...I just need to stop thinking out loud...";
D.q[5289] = "";
D.q[7325] = "";
D.q[4198] = "This creature is the one who gave birth to most of the living plants in this forest. Each petal, each stamen, each pollen grain that the Tynril loses will give birth to a new creature which will take its place in the island\'s food chain. Nowadays, this creature has become uncontrollable. When the Tynril was in the lab, we could at least check on any new creatures that were born.";
D.q[7326] = "";
D.q[7636] = "So, have you brought back everything I asked for?";
D.q[2310] = "I\'ll present you with the facts. The Enutrofs requested our help. For some time now, strange, frightening incidents have been taking place during their excavations. They sense danger, and where there\'s danger, hoho, you\'ll find a Iop! I believe you\'re now ready to lend them a hand. Go and find Gasdaure in the tunnels! But, by Iop, take care young one...";
D.q[2003] = "Some Dizbi extract! Wow! If you ever need anything, don\'t hesitate to ask. Besides, you might be interested in an insurance policy? No? Maybe next time... So, good nap! Ehhhh... luck, I mean, good luck!";
D.q[470] = "Good Heavens...You beat me good...I\'m gonna have a hawd time sitting down fow some time... Let me thank you fow this beautiful fight that weminded me of my youth...Choose between my staff, my cwown and my cloak, one of them can be youws...\nDon\'t hesitate to come back! We can teaw each othew apawt again!";
D.q[7327] = "";
D.q[33] = "Gah, I\'ve been bitten by those damned Moskitoes again... Mum tells me it\'s because of my peach-like complexion, my skin is too sweet... \nI think you might be able to help me.";
D.q[6134] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[7637] = "From what I\'ve heard, she\'s doing something over at the Militia. You should make your way over there if you want to speak to her.";
D.q[688] = "And here is the second question,\nHow can you measure the attention\nWithin a couple of lovers.\nIn terms of quantity, it would be better.";
D.q[2211] = "Three-Flower lives to the south. Ask at the Amakna village Inn, I\'m sure someone will be able to tell you where he\'s. He\'s bound to turn up there sooner or later, he always had a soft spot for beer!";
D.q[346] = "I have a few jobs I can offer you: Moskito extermination, collecting Treechnid Wood, carving a Treechnid Root Staff and the extermination of the Ancestral Treechnid.";
D.q[7328] = "";
D.q[3808] = "Fair deal! Here\'s your necklace.";
D.q[4035] = "Hello! I\'m happy to see you again my friend! Can you help me one more time?";
D.q[1741] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know?";
D.q[6564] = "Get down on all fours.";
D.q[1736] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[1732] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know?";
D.q[5128] = "";
D.q[7869] = "One day, when I\'m grown up, I\'m going to be a princess... That\'s what my daddy used to tell me before the big freeze. What\'s more, my friend Knil left me to be with Anope, who he thinks is prettier and he lost my Feca teddy. I hate him even more than the Count!";
D.q[7463] = "";
D.q[5354] = "";
D.q[2438] = "The workbenches where the meat is cut are in the scullery of the butcher\'s shop.";
D.q[3370] = "The world is full of weak fools. Are there no more true warriors?";
D.q[7870] = "Did you find it?\nThank you, thank you, thank you! You\'re so kind! Take this Ice Kama, I don\'t need it.";
D.q[90] = "Hello! I\'m Edrige Valling, the renowned archer. I\'d be more than happy to answer any questions you have about Bows or how they\'re made.";
D.q[2228] = "Ah, at last, the customer who ordered it left. I\'ll eat it myself then. There\'s no way I\'ll pay for the delivery!";
D.q[7871] = "Thank you for finding my teddy. Anope is jealous and is upset with Knil because he didn\'t get her one. Serves them right!";
D.q[6926] = "Hey, hey hey, calm down. What makes you think that I\'ll help you so easily? Freeing Nosilla Budois would be bad for business. If I locked her up, it was for good reason.";
D.q[1755] = "Xelors are very intelligent characters, but they\'re always looking for things to help them become smarter.";
D.q[7872] = "Hello, I\'m helping Aurora Borealis to create her Ice Village. I am a kind of technical director of the project.\nRight now, I\'m trying to modify a drill to suit our needs but at the same time I have plenty of other odd jobs to take care of. Of course, it\'s not like I have the same amount of manpower as the Count, or the mild weather, but I\'ll manage. Say, you wouldn\'t happen to have any chewing gum?";
D.q[2838] = "So you want to be a spy, do you? It\'s a good thing you\'re here, I\'ve a mission for you. \nYou must have heard that the Brakmarians have set fire to the Militia\'s Dragoturkey food stores. You must be wondering why they did that, no? Well now\'s your chance to find out. \nI want you to go to the Tower of Brakmar immediately and find out what the Brakmarians are up to.\nWhile you\'re there, pay a visit to Fidji Merline and give her this, she\'ll understand. Once she\'s read the letter, she\'ll tell you exactly what to do, you\'d better listen carefully. I\'m counting on you.";
D.q[4420] = "Can I help you?";
D.q[4223] = "Opinions diverge about this, but a terrible dragon is said to have tried to attack this creature.\nThen the creature got grip of the dragon with its tentacles, dragged and choked it in the peat catching it off its guard.\nDragons incarnate power and that\'s why a lot of people won\'t believe this story. But facts are there, a dragon carcass is really buried in this peat bog. ";
D.q[6085] = "The situation is only getting worse and this Assembly is only fanning the flames.";
D.q[7330] = "";
D.q[1200] = "Well, you wish to continue under my guardianship, within the Order of the Sharp Eye. Smart choice. You won\'t regret it. \nHowever, to confirm your membership you\'ll have to go find the clerk of the Order. Since his pet mouse left him, he spends his time at the Inn. Bring him back here and we\'ll get you in alright.";
D.q[128] = "Any kind of wood can be used to make a bow. Some woods are better than others, though, and it\'s not at all surprising that a bow made of Ash Wood is less efficient than a bow made of Yew Wood. The most efficient bows are in general composed of several types of wood, but these are both harder to make and harder to find materials for. Let\'s just say, you have to have some friends in the Lumberjack trade to get anything done.";
D.q[7873] = "Great! That\'s going to solve no end of problems. Did you know that this chewing gum can combine with other objects to make a snow propellant, a steering box for drills or even repair the plumbing system\'s thermostat?\nTake this Ice Kama, and if you find more chewing gum bring it to me straight away, ok?";
D.q[1745] = "Fecas are very intelligent characters but they\'re always looking for things to make them smarter.";
D.q[5357] = "";
D.q[3975] = "What? Kill Wabbit? No time, me give gifts to females.";
D.q[7874] = "I need a large variety of plants for crossbreeding to get new species which are both more resistant and multipurpose.\nSeveral Mastogobs have ravaged my greenhouse and have upset my Yucca Lilies. Ideally, I need 55 of these plants to have survived.\nI also need ten or so Osuction Tulips which grow in the fields and two Snowdrops.";
D.q[4046] = "Hello.";
D.q[5198] = "";
D.q[7332] = "";
D.q[7639] = "Hurry up, my preparations are progressing rapidly.";
D.q[4488] = "Sorry but I can\'t just give out that Sort of information.";
D.q[7875] = "I\'m so happy to have found someone I can trust. I hope you\'re not planning on changing sides. Whatever happens, thank you.\nDon\'t go too far because I might have to call on your services again soon.";
D.q[7331] = "";
D.q[7375] = "";
D.q[5356] = "";
D.q[6595] = "Pnj(1121) et Message(6594)";
D.q[7376] = "";
D.q[4794] = "So, have you found the person who, according to Nope, was following Kit Dingaround that day?\nI hope that child didn\'t just make the story up to try and save a friend.";
D.q[7640] = "Now that everything is in place, I need you to place this gold necklace on the grave of Goultard\'s mother, Cabotine.";
D.q[7876] = "The richness of the soil allowed for very intensive farming, but today very little remains to serve as a reminder. Winter has frozen the earth and killed off all the young shoots, and the snow has gradually covered all the vegetables trying to survive.\nModas Mimosas used to grow on the Lonesome Pine Trails, but these abundant flowers have practically disappeared nowadays. Nevertheless, I need to find about ten of them to create new plant hybrids. Could you take care of it, and at the same time bring me about sixty Nelson Roses? You will find some in the areas populated by the creatures of the forest.";
D.q[302] = "Go slipping through...";
D.q[621] = "An alchemist manipulates elements, either magic or not. He transforms materials. But don\'t see him as a labouratory rat. A real alchemist spends half of his time working in his atelier, and the other half travelling around the world searching for rare ingredients. And I can tell you from experience that when your reserve of Boowolf hair is empty, you\'ll have to take your courage in both hands to fill it again.";
D.q[7377] = "";
D.q[7641] = "That pleases me, the trap is set but there is still much to accomplish. As it will all take some time, I need your help. I have a lot of work, and obviously you are trustworthy. My mistress, the demoness Midnight, has told me about a vicious Bwork, who is an accomplished fighter. He could be of great use to my mistress, bring him to me while I finish my work.";
D.q[7877] = "I knew that the Modas Mimosas had survived. Thank you for your help.\nIf I ever complete my experiments, we will be able to send each other cereals and the famine will be nothing but a bad memory.";
D.q[7333] = "";
D.q[5470] = "What? You like pecan nut? Yum! Me prefer Aaaaapple!";
D.q[7642] = "Wot you want? Grabumph?!";
D.q[7878] = "I\'ve just understood something, if I want to become an expert in agriculture: I have to make the idea of eating plants more attractive than the idea of eating cereals, but how much of what already exists originates from plants? I\'m seriously considering using Ershop rhubarb to charm the consumers\' palates. It\'s a plant that only grows in the underground ice caves, which we can\'t get to. However, the Pingwins often bring some back with them, so that\'s our chance to get some. Can you go to the frozen lake and ask the Pingwins to give me 65 Ershop Rhubarbs?";
D.q[5732] = "Wonderful. It takes courage and skill to successfully steal such an item from the Tower of Brakmar. You definitely deserve to become Supreme Assassin.";
D.q[7334] = "";
D.q[7378] = "";
D.q[7643] = "Me beaten, me prisoner. You leave village, me follow.";
D.q[7879] = "You\'re a very gifted negotiator, that\'s for sure. Count Harebourg was too and that was what enabled him to win the agricultural invention competition by proposing a revolutionary machine: a giant geothermic extractor calibrated to the seasons which kept the crops warm using steam during the cold seasons. What\'s more, it\'s where the system we currently use in our greenhouses comes from.";
D.q[6737] = "A little break, a quick snack... no harm in that, is there. Don\'t you have anything to eat yourself? I\'ve a whole pile of golden brioches, jam and lots more besides. Do you want some? Well... too bad, you should have bought some before we left";
D.q[5436] = "";
D.q[7880] = "Lots of people abandon their familiars or their pets. Since the winter, this has become less common in Frigost because the animals can\'t survive more than a couple of days. When the ice village is finished, I will build a pet sanctuary to look after all these poor creatures.";
D.q[5847] = "";
D.q[4190] = "So you want to get into this huge stinky cave...\nI hope you know what you\'re doing!\nAnd you must know that I won\'t let you in unless you can give me the key. I lost it somewhere on the Coral beach and I think that the creatures living around there took it.";
D.q[3696] = "Highly experienced harvesters gather a lot of resources at a time... a lot more than beginners at least!";
D.q[86] = "I don\'t sell boots to just anyone who passes by, what do you take me for?";
D.q[7881] = "I\'m preparing myself by adopting orphaned Pingwinkles after their mother has been killed by the fishermen and the continentals.\nI just have a few that I don\'t really have time to take care of anymore and who might run away. I could give you one in exchange for an Icefish.";
D.q[7379] = "";
D.q[101] = "Hi! I\'m selling my husband\'s Pickaxe, if you\'re interested... Good general state, rarely used...";
D.q[5528] = "And sign once more on the register. If you don\'t sign, I\'ll have to cancel the whole process. And you won\'t get your money back, either.";
D.q[5947] = "";
D.q[1484] = "A larva? What are you talking about...? Ahhh, a golden larva! A legendary creature indeed! According to the stories, these are very young specimens... AH! Anyway, we don\'t have time for that. You must bring this larva back to its parents before they come here to get it themselves.";
D.q[7884] = "My family jewels, you\'ve found them! My wife will be made up, by the way.\nTake this Purse of Kamas and don\'t tell anyone.";
D.q[6927] = "We Xelors use our mastery of time to glimpse the past, present and future, and it is through this that we make our guesses, but the power of Nosilla Dubois is quite different. That Sacrier has special powers of divination. Somehow she is able to make contact with souls.\nHer power allows her to know things that our mastery of time does not reveal, so straight away some potential customers would rather go and see her.";
D.q[4191] = "Poor Great Coralator, he didn\'t survive long. But for all that I\'m not impressed!\nTake these two presents in exchange for your key, they\'ll be very useful.";
D.q[402] = "Shush! Quiet! You\'re in a library here. If you need a book, ask me. But no talking! Sssshhh, I said no talking. Go and sit down but don\'t make a sound. \nI don\'t want to hear another peep out of you. \nNot even a whisper.";
D.q[6605] = "";
D.q[7885] = "Can I touch it?\nOooh, I\'m impressed. I\'ve never seen anything so big and hard. Supple and solid at the same time, it must melt in your mouth. I\'m all excited!\nYou did me a service, which is why I\'m going to ask my friend at Ego Flagship and Sons to let you use his carrier if you want to go to Alma\'s Cradle.";
D.q[6606] = "";
D.q[2707] = "A long time ago, the Lenalds wele the plotectols of a Dofus. Envied by the Pandawas of Feudala, they plotted with those vile Wabbits! And we, the Lenalds, wele kicked off oul own island... As for the Dofus, no one knows what happened to it... One thing is sule - neithel the File Pandawas nol the Pandikazes have it. They would have said it to evelyone! The Pandawas of Akwadala ale my fwiends. Those fwom Aerdala lemain... You would be doing me a gleat favol if you could go have a look... You\'re still hele? What ale you waiting fol?";
D.q[4819] = "";
D.q[7337] = "";
D.q[729] = "A man is holding a fair in the plains. I\'d like you to check the place out and make sure it\'s not a new stratagem of our enemies to hide a camp near Bonta. \n\nTalk to Ture Inge, he makes infallible tests to detect Brakmarians.";
D.q[6928] = "Whom do you take me for? I wanted to get rid of that annoyance, certainly, but not to become a murderer. That\'s why I looked for susceptible people who could help me shut her away indefinitely. You could say that ten years alone in this cave is just the same...\nWell, okay, you win. I am willing to give you the information necessary to free her, but on one condition: you must make Nosilla Budois promise never to set foot in Astrub or its vicinity, that way I\'ll keep my clients.";
D.q[6607] = "";
D.q[1769] = "A few years ago, Fecas only used Gobballs to train for combat. But, not long ago, we discovered a race called Dopples and they basically live to fight. They\'re good training opponents no matter what your level is.";
D.q[7886] = "What\'s missing from Frigost is another big project. Before, activity on the island revolved around agricultural exportation. That hasn\'t been the case for a while, and now we spend our time trying to thaw out the port, all because of the Count. I\'d really like a new challenge.";
D.q[5001] = "";
D.q[848] = "Some of the cartel guys are really starting to... hmm... appreciate your work. Well, since you\'re so good I\'ll give you more difficult missions. Ah, I\'ve just devised the perfect test for your level passage. Go and take out 5 Bontarian militiamen and bring me their badg...oh no, I\'d rather have their shorts, heheh.";
D.q[293] = "I\'ll give you one unit of wheatmeal. But you can also have the privilege of testing a prototype of my Curryless Curry Bread, the effect is not guaranteed, but it might surprise you. I\'d normally use my apprentice to test prototypes, but he\'s been unusually reluctant this past few days.";
D.q[6033] = "";
D.q[4831] = "Do I really have to stay here with this Sram who smells of rotten fish?";
D.q[5857] = "";
D.q[3672] = "Ah my dear... how skilled you are, you have reason to be proud. Soon, you may even possess a Dofus. If you\'re so lucky, my dear, take care of it... don\'t let it break... let me tell you, you can\'t even make an omelette with the inside of these eggs! Guard it with your life.";
D.q[643] = "With the sweet breeze sweeping through your hair, weapon in hand, a grin on your lips, intense battle excitement, adrenalin rising when you strike your enemy... Oh, sorry, I didn\'t see you...\n\nHi young adventurer! I\'m the guardian of Tainela.\nMy brothers must have started training you already.\nSo you\'re looking forward to exploring Amakna...\nChoose your profession soon. Go explore new territories, and try to master as many spells and types of equipment as you can...\nAlways be careful in this world and mistrust the dark side of other adventurers.";
D.q[7888] = "At the beginning, I hated him for having destroyed so many vegetables. Later, I discovered the charm of the snow-covered earth and now, I wish with all my heart that winter would last an eternity.";
D.q[4194] = "One day, while we were anchored by Moon Island, vile pirates stole into the hold. They attacked us as soon as we arrived on this island. They left the hold in the middle of the night, and killed almost all of my crew. They took control of the ship but their captain didn\'t know the difference between port and starboard, so they ran aground in this peat bog, and decided to settle here for the rest of their lives. ";
D.q[5457] = "";
D.q[7887] = "I wasn\'t expecting a continental to come to our rescue!\nWe\'ve got a lot of work to do but we need more manpower and skilled workers. We need to convince Mayor Cantile to let us recruit more villagers. Do you think you would be able to do that for us, please? I\'ve got too much to do myself and the Mayor is not very fond of Aurora and her pro-winter ideas.";
D.q[5412] = "";
D.q[7427] = "";
D.q[5858] = "";
D.q[1397] = "...";
D.q[1798] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Ecaflip temple. \nIt will cost you a piece of Claw\'s Jigsaw.";
D.q[3407] = "The Key Master told me of your victory. I didn\'t believe in you... I apologize. I\'ll keep my promise, however. Here, wrap your greedy hands round our family relic. Many warriors have built their name on this ancient pedestal! Be warned that a terrible curse will strike the fool who turns it over! Make good use of it!";
D.q[5364] = "";
D.q[7889] = "Aurora Borealis has some odd ideas. Our goal is to rid ourselves of the curse of the eternal winter. When we manage it, her ice village project will fall through. I don\'t see any point in wasting time and manpower on a project which is doomed to failure.\nI know that after a century of the big freeze, some people no longer share my point of view, but if they want to waste their time, that\'s their problem.";
D.q[268] = "Persuading beginners with words takes far too long. Go talk to Juhdo Pull in the basement, and ask him to train you up.";
D.q[168] = "Ever since the brewery was been destroyed by a thirsty Crackler, the Brewers have been out of work. The manager of the Tavern decided to lend them the cellar so that they can set up a new brewery and keep on producing their marvellous beer. \nI hope they get to work soon... our beer supplies are decreasing by the minute!";
D.q[362] = "Hello. My name is Ronsha Nesto. I\'m a widow... In fact I\'m a widow four times over. All my husbands were found dead, a Prespic Peak to the heart each time. It\'s awful really. And the authorities have never managed to find the Prespic behind these horrors.";
D.q[7890] = "It might seem odd, more odd than the port thawing in any case, but I\'m afraid of being attacked on the way. Could you come with me, please?";
D.q[4509] = "Hello, have you spoken to Justfa Lafs in the Tower of Orders? Patience isn\'t his strong point so I suggest you get there in plenty of time.";
D.q[4690] = "";
D.q[4781] = "Well... I... you know... I wanted to catch him red-handed... you know?";
D.q[1832] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sadida temple.\nIt will cost you a Wild Sunflower leaf.";
D.q[2448] = "Indeed, each time you lose a fight, you also lose some of your Energy. You\'d better be warned that if you\'re not careful enough, you\'ll end up in the other world. Some say certain persons know how to handle the Energy using enchanted potions and breads.";
D.q[7647] = "You think I have nothing else to do but listen to your prayers? Get out of my sight.";
D.q[7891] = "The other madwoman wants to steal my sailors and dockers to work on her insane ice village project? It\'s out of the question, I refuse to allow anyone in my charge go and work there. I need everyone here and I\'m not going to obey her like some good little Bow Wow just because mademoiselle is an aristocrat.\nHave I made myself clear?";
D.q[5864] = "";
D.q[2011] = "The Iops already know about it? By the Twelve! Just needs the Sacriers... I really have to take care of everything around here! A safe, and now bodyguards...";
D.q[4903] = "So, did you find the Hammer of Light?";
D.q[7892] = "What do you take me for? I\'m not an employment agency. Although...\nListen, We can talk about the need for manpower to build a village made of ice, but in exchange, you have to promise to do something for me.\nWhat do you say?";
